    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">ann</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2006/04/spring-sliced-and-straight-from-the-bowl/#comment-3361"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-06-23T17:01:00-04:00">Wednesday, June 23, 2010 at 5:01 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>So many years after the post&#8230; I just wanted to let you know that I have been making this salad every week since February. Now it&#39;s June and there is no end to my devotion in sight. It&#39;s pretty much always the same. Sometimes I add a poached egg, sometimes I substitute shaved parmesan. It never ever ever gets old. Thank you thank you thank you.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-3362" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Bobo</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2006/04/spring-sliced-and-straight-from-the-bowl/#comment-3362"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-07-13T22:39:05-04:00">Tuesday, July 13, 2010 at 10:39 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>i am of the same ilk- if you like it, eat it every day til you can&#39;t any more!! and, i&#39;ve been making this a lot lately. i am barbara of barbara and victoria of the umeboshi and varied vinegars!! i dream of delancy a lot. it was so wonderful. i can&#39;t wait to come back. i&#39;m also making caramelized cauliflower tonight, july or no&#8230;.because i can&#39;t get enough of that either&#8230;in all of its different incarnations&#8230;with chick peas, curry, shallots&#8230;red onions&#8230;you are the best, molly!!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-3363" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2006/04/spring-sliced-and-straight-from-the-bowl/#comment-3363"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-01-10T00:26:50-05:00">Saturday, January 10, 2015 at 12:26 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Keeping the thread alive!  After many iterations of this salad, may I recommend people try it with lentils or farro; toasted pumpkin seeds or pistachios; pink or red grapefruit; and/or rye croutons. It&#39;s the grapefruit, though, that really sends it over the moon. A real table-pounder. Thanks, Molly! &#8211; chloe</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    </ol>

      
  
